        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "What is the Subjunctive?",
        "content": "The subjunctive is not a tense but a MOOD. It expresses subjectivity: wishes, doubts, emotions, possibilities, and hypotheticals. The indicative states facts; the subjunctive expresses non-facts."
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "The WEIRDO Triggers",
        "content": "Subjunctive is triggered by these categories in the main clause:\n                              → D - Doubt/Denial = dudar que, no creer que",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "W - Wishes/Wants",
            "english": "querer que, desear que, preferir que"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "E - Emotions",
            "english": "alegrarse de que, tener miedo de que"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "I - Impersonal expressions",
            "english": "es importante que, es necesario que"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "R - Recommendations",
            "english": "recomendar que, sugerir que"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "D - Doubt/Denial",
            "english": "dudar que, no creer que"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Forming Present Subjunctive",
        "content": "Start with yo form of present indicative, drop -o, add opposite endings:\n            → -ER/-IR verbs: -a, -as, -a, -amos, -an = coma, comas, coma, comamos, coman",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "-AR verbs: -e, -es, -e, -emos, -en",
            "english": "hable, hables, hable, hablemos, hablen"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "-ER/-IR verbs: -a, -as, -a, -amos, -an",
            "english": "coma, comas, coma, comamos, coman"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "HABLAR in Subjunctive",
        "content": "From hablo                               \n   ✏️ Exercise: Quiero que tú ___ español. (hablar)",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "yo hable",
            "english": "that I speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "tú hables",
            "english": "that you speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "él/ella hable",
            "english": "that he/she speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "nosotros hablemos",
            "english": "that we speak"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "ellos hablen",
            "english": "that they speak"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Subjunctive with Wishes",
        "content": "When the subjects are different, use subjunctive after que:\n                  → Espero que llueva = I hope it rains",
        "examples": [
          {
            "spanish": "Quiero que vengas",
            "english": "I want you to come"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Deseo que seas feliz",
            "english": "I wish you to be happy"
          },
          {
            "spanish": "Espero que llueva",
            "english": "I hope it rains"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "lesson",
        "heading": "Irregular Subjunctives",
        "content": "Common irregular verbs:\n                              \n   ✏️ Exercise: Match subjunctive forms:",
        "examples": [
